result.execSummary:
The defendant Virgil Ewing was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Attempt Mayhem [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.21.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Defendant Virgil Ewing in court with attorney Robert Gerald Lebell.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by Latoya L and Ora E.  Case passed to allow the court to review medical reports.
Case recalled.  Sentencing proceeded.    
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 15 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 3 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 5 YEARS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-The court is ordering that $1600.00 for child support arrearrages be taken from cash bail on deposit Forthwith.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
-ABSOLUTE NO CONTACT with victim, Latoya L.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
The court, however, has no objection if the defendant participates in the programs.
Defendant remanded.

Defendant Virgil Ewing in court with attorney Robert Gerald Lebell.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  AS to count 3 as charged:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  
Counts 1,2,4,5 are ordered dismissed and read in for sentencing.  The state is requesting that the defendant be remanded pending sentencing.  Defense objects.  The court will maintain the same conditions of bail and adjourn sentencing to 12-22-2015.  Trial date of 11-16-2015 is vacated.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 22, 2015 at 08:15 am.
